{"word":"τιμήεις","slug":"τιμήεις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τιμήεις</b></el> <el>(τῑμήεις, εσσα, εν) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>honoured, esteemed</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a>, <el>τιμηέστερος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>prized, costly</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>τιμηέστατος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}